  <h1>Privacy</h1>
  <p> Nicholis du Toit (hereinafter &quot;TrueWinter&quot;, &quot;we&quot;, &quot;us&quot;, &quot;I&quot;, &quot;me&quot;) is committed to protecting your privacy and developing technology that gives you the most powerful and safe online experience. This Statement of Privacy applies to the TrueWinter website and governs data collection and usage. By using the TrueWinter website, you consent to the data practices described in this statement. </p>
  <h2>Collection of your Personal Information</h2>
  <p> TrueWinter collects personally identifiable information, such as your e-mail address, name, home or work address or telephone number. TrueWinter also collects anonymous demographic information, which is not unique to you, such as your Postal code, age, gender, preferences, interests and favourites. There is also information about your computer hardware and software that is automatically collected by TrueWinter. This information can include: your IP address, browser type, domain names, access times and referring website addresses. This information is used by TrueWinter for the operation of the service, to maintain quality of the service, and to provide general statistics regarding use of the TrueWinter website. Please keep in mind that if you directly disclose personally identifiable information or personally sensitive data through TrueWinter public message boards, this information may be collected and used by others. Note: TrueWinter does not read any of your private online communications. TrueWinter encourages you to review the privacy statements of websites you choose to link to from TrueWinter, so that you can understand how those websites collect, use and share your information. TrueWinter is not responsible for the privacy statements or other content on websites outside of the TrueWinter and family of websites. </p>
  <h2>Use of your Personal Information</h2>
  <p> TrueWinter collects the following: </p>
  <ul>
    <li>IP Addresses: Your IP address may be logged to help us identify most common times of activity and for<br>tracking intrusion attempts and DDoS attempts. <strong>This information is kept for 7 days, but may be kept as long as it is needed when investigating security incidents or server issues.</strong><br></li>
    <li>Email Addresses, Names: This information is used to respond to enquiries. <strong>This is kept for as long as it is needed.</strong><br></li>
    <li>Website usage data: How you interact with the website is tracked (pages visited, the duration of the visit, previous visits), how you access the website (device information, time accessed, city, how you found the website, web browser, operating system) are collected. This is done through a third-party service called Cloudflare Analytics (view their privacy policy <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/en-gb/privacypolicy/">here</a>). This information is used to provide general statistics and to maintain quality of service.<br></li>
    <li>Comment Data: If you leave a comment on the blog, this information, as well as your IP address and user agent, is sent to Akismet for the purposes of spam filtering. You can read more about how they process your data at&#xA0;<a href="https://akismet.com/privacy/">https://akismet.com/privacy/</a>. Comment data is stored in a database to allow for retrieval and display of comments on the blog. This data is stored in a MongoDB Atlas cluster in Germany and <strong>is kept indefinitely</strong>. Your IP address and user agent are not stored, and your email address is only stored as a hash to show Gravatar images next to your comments.</li>
